{meta: title Shoes Of A Fool}
{meta: artist Charlie Walker}
{meta: composer Jim Coleman and Jimmy Day}

{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[C]See them walking down the street
Shinny bright and very neat
Those are shoes of a [G7]fool
See them through that swinging door
[C]Right across that barroom floor
[D7]Those are the [G7]shoes of a [C]fool
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
That [F]small and dated pair back 
Walked [C]beside them for so long
And [G7]never had an awful lot to [C]say
Got [F]tired of all those neon lights
And [C]all those lies and sleepless nights
Just [D7]up and clicked her heels and walked [G7]away
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
[C]See once where were air is stale
The other hanging on the rail
Those are the shoes of a [G7]fool
Acting witty wise and smart
[C]Just to hide a broken heart
[D7]Those are the [G7]shoes of a [C]fool
{end_of_verse}

